{
  "guid": "musw",
  "name": "Multi-Switch",
  "description": "This algorithm offers up to six highly configurable sequential or voltage-controlled switches that are DC-coupled and can handle both audio and CV signals. Each switch consists of two sub-switches: an input sub-switch and an output sub-switch, where the selected input is routed to the selected output. When multiple switches share the same output, their signals are summed. Each sub-switch supports crossfading for click-free transitions or noticeable blends between sources/targets. The switches can be controlled by CV inputs or via 'Macro' parameters, which can be mapped to various control sources like CV, MIDI, or I2C.",
  "categories": [
